  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 236220 federal contract obligations for FY2026 to date total $39.7B across 11,978 awards, with an average award size of $3.3M and year-over-year change up 29.6%. Obligations climbed from $23B in FY21 through a multi-year rise to $32.9B in FY23, dipped to $30.9B in FY24 and $30.6B in FY25, and then increased to $39.7B in FY26. The Department of Homeland Security accounted for the largest share of FY2026 obligations at $28.4B, followed by the Department of Defense at $6.6B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $2B. Vendor concentration is notable: FISHER SAND & GRAVEL CO received $13.3B in obligations, BARNARD CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, INCORPORATED received $4.5B, and SLS FEDERAL SERVICES LLC and SPENCER CONSTRUCTION LLC each received $2.4B. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) and represent obligations recorded so far in FY2026.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How large is the FY2026 federal market for NAICS 236220?",
        "body": "The FY2026 to date market for NAICS 236220 totals $39.7B in obligations across 11,978 awards with an average award size of $3.3M. Obligations are up 29.6% year over year and represent the highest annual total shown compared with FY21–FY25."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who dominates buying and contracting in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Homeland Security is the dominant buyer at $28.4B, followed by the Department of Defense at $6.6B and the Department of Veterans Affairs at $2B. On the vendor side, FISHER SAND & GRAVEL CO leads with $13.3B in obligations, with BARNARD CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, INCORPORATED at $4.5B and multiple firms including SLS FEDERAL SERVICES LLC and SPENCER CONSTRUCTION LLC each at $2.4B."
      }
    ]
